<P>
   WAR-RULES (San Francisco) _ War, like other human institutions,
has evolved in the 20th century. The century that began with ``the
war to end all wars'' moved on to ``genocide'' and ended with
``ethnic cleansing.'' Alongside the evolution of warfare, another
20th-century idea has developed: Rules for warfare and the
treatment of combatants and civilians. By GAIL BENSINGER.
</P>
<P>
   RU-286 (San Francisco) _ Why are American women so behind the
times? We are supposed to have the most advanced medical system in
the world, but the abortion pill, RU-486, is still not available in
this country. By MARGOT MAGOWAN.
</P>
