<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SAM-PHILLIPS-REVIEW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SAM HAD HIS DAY IN THE SUN
</HEADLINE>
  (For use on June 18 by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below; `tonight' refers to Sun. June 18) 
Our rating: 3 stars 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Rock biographer Peter Guralnick, whose Elvis Presley books
``Last Train to Memphis'' and ``Careless Love'' are considered
essential examples of the genre, turns his attentions to the man
who discovered the King in ``Sam Phillips: The Man Who Invented
Rock 'n' Roll,`` a new A&AMP;E ``Biography.''
</P>
<P>
   Guralnick serviceably hits all the high points. These include
Phillips' early radio career and his opening the Memphis Recording
Service (which would soon become Sun Records) in 1950. There's the
discovery, in addition to Presley, of Howling Wolf, Johnny Cash,
Roy Orbison, Carl Perkins and Jerry Lee Lewis; the impromptu
million-dollar session which included most of the above-mentioned
artists; and, finally, the selling Presley's contract for $35,000
and, a dozen years later, the Sun catalog for $1 million.
</P>
<P>
   But Guralnick also mines the quirkier elements of Phillips'
career: Starting up WHER, the first all-woman radio station; his
early investments in Holiday Inn, which really made him a wealthy
man; and his friendship with a pro wrestler and avid segregationist
named Sputnick Monroe. Curiously, he brings up an affair Phillips
once had without eliciting comment from the producer or his wife,
who both participated in the project and speak at length on other
subjects _ it's like an editorial rap on the knuckles, followed by
a winking silence.
</P>
<P>
   To this day, Phillips remains an engaging raconteur. He and
other interviewees display lingering enthusiasm, and the
well-chosen archival pieces _ old songs, home movies, TV clips and
audio transcriptions _ are given ample air time to convey their
glorious essence. ``Sam Phillips,'' as well as almost any document
out there, captures the energy, excitement and pure joy of those
early days of rock. &QL; 
--- &QL; 
The show: ``Sam Phillips: The Man Who Invented Rock `n' Roll.'' &QL; 
What: ``Biography'' on the legendary producer. &QL; 
Who: Narrated by Billy Bob Thornton. &QL; 
Where: A&AMP;E. &QL; 
When: 8 tonight. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-15-00 1225EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
