relatives said at a rambling news briefing that they have met the
deadline to file a petition for a rehearing of their case in the
battle to keep the 6-year-old Cuban boy in this country. The
request for a rehearing before all 12 judges of the 11th U.S.
Circuit Court of Appeals in Atlanta was sent to the court overnight
and was expected to arrive later Thursday, attorneys for the family
said. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
