   GORE-COELHO _ CINCINNATI - Vice President Al Gore's campaign
underwent its second major shakeup Thursday with the resignation of
Tony Coelho from the top spot. Coelho, who has been dogged by
ethical questions, stepped down for health reasons. His replacement
will be Commerce Secretary William Daley, who will leave his
Clinton cabinet post to direct the Gore presidential campaign
during the final six months of the contest. With comments from
Gore, Coelho and Bush campaign reaction. (Shepard, Cox News
Service)
