<P>
   DAVIS-SEA-PAINTINGS (New York) _ At first look, the quaint
fishing port of Gloucester, Mass., seems an unlikely hangout for
the jazzy city painter Stuart Davis (1894-1964). But according to
``Stuart Davis in Gloucester,'' a show of some 45 oils, watercolors
and drawings at the National Academy of Design, Gloucester and its
well-worn motifs play a role in the lively and innovative American
Cubist style that Davis eventually developed. By Grace Glueck.
</P>
