<P>
   RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-EARNHARDT _ Dale Earnhardt is in prime position to win an
eighth Winston Cup championship, which would break his tie with
Richard Petty in the history books. This could turn out to be one
of the biggest stories in NASCAR in years, and nobody is more
excited about it than track officials _ including those at AMS _
who could see record tickets sales if the Intimidator stays in
contention. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
