   INVEST-NEWSLETTERS (Undated) _ For 20 years Mark Hulbert has
been monitoring investment newsletters. Now he has done a
comparison of those that deliver advice via e-mail, fax and hot
lines and those that use conventional mail. He concludes there is
no difference in investment performance: a 10.9 percent annualized
return for the quick delivery group, versus 10.5 percent for the
regular-mail group. Why? Quick information leads to quick exits in
a field that benefits from longterm relationships. &QL;
