<P>
   PIPELINE-SAFETY (Washington) _ The federal agency responsible
for pipeline safety is a weak, overly compliant regulator that
seldom imposes fines when violations are found, and even then often
doesn't bother to collect them, an independent study of the agency
concludes. The report by the General Accounting Office also charges
that the Office of Pipeline Safety fails to fully involve state
officials and ignores reforms demanded by Congress.
