<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-15 19:31 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5126 &Cx1f; tic-z
u v BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR &LR;      06-15 0106
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, June 16. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
REUNION (Undated) - A Mexican baby girl who survived the Arizona
desert was scheduled to be reunited with her grandmother in Mexico
Thursday. The baby's mother, crossing illegally to find her husband
in Oregon, died in the desert after giving her daughter her last
drop of water. By MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the `A`
category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
