</P>
<P>
   GORE-COELHO (Washington) _ In yet another reshuffling of his
presidential campaign, Vice President Al Gore announces that Bill
Daley, the secretary of commerce and a shrewd operative in
Democratic politics, will replace the campaign chairman, Tony
Coelho. Coelho, who was hospitalized Monday night with an inflamed
colon, said he decided to step down on the advice of his doctors,
but many Democrats said the move was not a huge surprise, given the
way Gore's campaign has been struggling. By Richard L. Berke.
