 PERSONALS: House of Clinton a House Divided? 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news
file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
Friends of  &UR; Bill &LR;  and  &UR; Hillary Clinton &LR;  told U.S. News &AMP; World
Report that if the Mrs. is elected to the Senate, Socks the cat
will live with her in Washington, and Buddy the dog will stay with
Bill Clinton at his museum and library in Little Rock.
</P>
<P>
   That would leave the New York house empty during the week, but
presumably all animals and adults would weekend in the new love
nest.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
