Kelsey Grammer and Diane Venora, as Lady Macbeth, in the
blunt-witted new production of ``Macbeth'' that opens Thursday
night at the Music Box Theater under the direction of Terry Hands.
During the play one doesn't think, ``Hey, look at old Frasier up
there.'' But on the other hand, you never for a second think that a
complicated, conflicted character named Macbeth is up on the stage
either, just an actor speaking lines in a melodious bass voice.
(Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
