   (NYT7) UNDATED -- June 15, 2000 -- PORTUGUESE-MODERNIST --
Modernism may or may not be over, but that hasn't kept historians
from adding names to its roster. With more and more names from more
parts of the world, it is at last being defined as a multinational,
multicultural phenomenon, which it always was. ``Leap of the
Rabbit,'' a 1911 painting by Amadeo de Souza Cardosa (1887-1918),
is among the works in his retrospective, ``At the Edge: A
Portuguese Futurist,'' on view in Manhattan at the AXA Gallery.
(AXA Gallery/The New York Times)
