 &UR; UNITED _ &LR;  United Airlines reaffirmed its pledge to decrease flight
delays at San Francisco International Airport by as much as 30
percent by this fall. During a wide-ranging discussion with
reporters Thursday, United Airlines President Rono J. Dutta said
the carrier would attempt to reduce delays by cutting back on the
number of its flights, reducing turn-around times for planes on the
ground and scheduling more flights during off-peak periods.
 &UR; BY PHAT X. CHIEM &LR;
